On your Ubuntu machine:

bash
Copy
Edit
sudo apt update
sudo apt install podman -y  # or docker if preferred
Then run a RHEL-compatible container:

bash
Copy
Edit
podman run -it --name rhel8-download --volume $HOME/rhel8_rpms:/rpms centos:8 bash
Inside the container:

bash
Copy
Edit
dnf install -y dnf-utils
dnf install --downloadonly --downloaddir=/rpms \
  kernel-devel-4.18.0-372.26.1.el8_6 \
  kernel-headers-4.18.0-372.26.1.el8_6 \
  gcc make binutils elfutils-libelf-devel
This downloads all required .rpm files into ~/rhel8_rpms on your Ubuntu system.

